<p>So, I was following this <a href="https://code.tutsplus.com/courses/build-a-microblogging-app-with-flux-and-react" rel="nofollow">tutorial</a> and an older version of react router was used there, so I figured I will try and implement the new syntax myself, but it is not working out.</p>  <p>Here's the deal:</p>  <pre><code>React.render(&lt;Router&gt;{routes}&lt;/Router&gt;, document.getElementById('app')); </code></pre>  <p>The routes are here:</p>  <pre><code>routes = (         &lt;Route path='*' component={require('./components/App')}&gt;             &lt;Route name="home" path="/" component={require('./components/Home')} /&gt;         &lt;/Route&gt;     ); </code></pre>  <p>And my App.js:</p>  <pre><code>var React = require('react'),      App = React.createClass({         render: function () {             return (                 &lt;div className="container"&gt;                     &lt;div className="row"&gt;                         &lt;h1&gt;chrpr&lt;/h1&gt;                     &lt;/div&gt;                     &lt;div className="row"&gt;                         &lt;div className="three columns"&gt;                             Navigation                         &lt;/div&gt;                         &lt;div className="nine columns"&gt;                             {this.props.children}                         &lt;/div&gt;                     &lt;/div&gt;                 &lt;/div&gt;             )         }     });  module.exports = App; </code></pre>  <p>In the tutorial he used the RouteHandler, which doesn't exists anymore so from what I understood I was just supposed to replace it with                                 <code>{this.props.children}</code>, which is really not doing anything, that part is empty.</p>  <p>What gives?</p>